verbLexeme: 1. To put your belongings into a bag, because you are leaving a place or going on holiday. English = pack, pack up.
2. To work as a packer in a process line in a factory.
nominalLexeme: 1. A person who removes things from the end of the process line in a factory and places them in packets or boxes. English = packer.
oldEntry: Popular explanation: putting things into a suitcase.
